{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491102","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491102"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:32:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:32:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"831"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"831","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/831"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.07,0.63,0.04,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"831"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43459"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"831","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/831"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"831"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28444"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"247"},{"type":"tags","id":"262"},{"type":"tags","id":"2044"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"11063"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5011"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5012"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29123"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44571"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45058"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43459","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43459"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 27-year-old woman presents to her General Practitioner with a three-week history of a lump in her right breast. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination the lump is firm, well circumscribed and mobile. There are no other abnormalities in either breast or axillae.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reassurance and review in one month","Mammography","Ultrasound","Fine needle aspiration cytology","Surgical excision"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhilst this is most likely to be a benign fibroadenoma, all breast lumps should be evaluated with the \u201ctriple test\u201d \u2013 clinical examination, imaging (via mammography and/or ultrasound), and biopsy. In this situation, where a lump has already been identified, referral for \u003Cstrong\u003Eultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E is most appropriate as a biopsy can be performed under ultrasound guidance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReassurance\u003C/strong\u003E alone is inappropriate without further investigation, as malignancy must be excluded even when the clinical presentation is more typical of a benign lump. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA diagnostic \u003Cstrong\u003Emammography\u003C/strong\u003E is less preferred in women \u0026lt;35 years old compared to ultrasound. Ultrasound is more sensitive in younger women, largely because the more fibrous breast tissue can obscure masses on mammography. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFine needle aspiration\u003C/strong\u003E (FNA) may be considered but is typically less favoured when compared with a core biopsy due to lower sensitivity. A key exception is when the ultrasound demonstrates a simple cyst, which may be better sampled using FNA. Regardless of the biopsy method chosen, this woman will need an ultrasound to guide the biopsy. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESurgical excision\u003C/strong\u003E is inappropriate in this patient given the lump is most likely benign and has not been investigated yet.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Ultrasound is the preferred imaging investigation of solitary breast swellings in young women."],"references":["The investigation of a new breast symptom: a guide for General Practitioners. In: Cancer Australia [online]. 2017. Available at: https://www.canceraustralia.gov.au/inbsguide"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28444"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"831"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28444","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/28444"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-03-18T11:04:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-20T14:28:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"831"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43459"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe0f","name":"Radiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-15T15:37:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null}